= Executive Summary

Bonu has evolved from a traditional Vietnamese food business into a modern F&B education and product platform. The new business model embraces the "Marketing Playground" philosophy - giving customers the freedom to choose what they want, when they want it, rather than forcing them into rigid packages.

== Core Philosophy: The Marketing Playground

*"Nobody wants to be sold to, but everybody loves to buy."*

Traditional education models push students through fixed curricula. The Playground Model invites customers to explore, sample, and choose their own journey. This creates genuine engagement and trust.

== The Three-Tier Strategy

=== Tier 0: FREE (Trust Building)
Build massive trust without any sales pressure. Give value freely to establish credibility.

=== Tier 1: TRIAL (The Costco Chicken)
Offer an irresistible taster at £15-20 that delivers exceptional value. This is your "loss leader" that proves quality.

=== Tier 2: PLAYGROUND (Freedom to Choose)
Let customers build their own curriculum by choosing individual workshops at £20 each. No pressure, total flexibility.

#pagebreak()

= The New Business Model

== Tier 0: FREE - Building Trust Without Agenda

=== Free Offerings

*1. Free Workshops*
- Completely free, no hidden agenda
- High-quality content delivery
- Zero sales pitch during the workshop
- Focus: Provide genuine value and education

*2. Digital Content*
- PDF guides on Vietnamese cuisine
- Ebooks on F&B business strategies
- Recipe collections
- Instagram/Facebook educational content
- YouTube cooking tutorials

*3. WhatsApp Community*
- Exclusive "F&B Community Group"
- Invitation-only (from free workshop attendees)
- Higher quality content than public social media
- Peer support and networking
- Bo's insights and tips shared regularly

=== The Free Workshop Strategy

*What we DO*:
- Deliver exceptional educational content
- Answer questions thoroughly
- Build genuine relationships
- Invite people to join WhatsApp community

*What we DON'T do*:
- NO sales pitches
- NO package offers
- NO pressure tactics
- NO "special deals"

*Why this works*:
- Creates trust through genuine value
- Removes resistance and skepticism
- Makes attendees WANT more (instead of feeling sold)
- Builds a qualified community of interested prospects

=== Critical Rule: Never Sell in Free

If something is labeled "free," it must BE free. Selling in a free workshop destroys trust instantly. The Vietnamese F&B community has attended hundreds of workshops - they can smell a sales pitch from miles away.

*The Reality*:
- People register thinking it's free
- They attend with enthusiasm
- Then comes the sales pitch
- Result: "Never see you again"

*Our Approach*:
- It's free, period
- Value delivered completely
- Only soft invitation to join community
- Trust = future business

#pagebreak()

== Tier 1: TRIAL - The £15-20 Gateway

=== The Costco Chicken Strategy

Think of Costco's famous rotisserie chicken: \$4.99, delicious, probably sold at a loss. People come for the chicken, leave with a cart full of groceries.

*Our Version*:
- One workshop session: £15-20
- Exceptional quality (worth £50+)
- Highly specialized topic
- Limited attendance for intimacy
- Might operate at break-even or small loss

=== What Makes It Irresistible

*Price Psychology*:
- £20 = "Won't even think about it" (cost of a meal)
- £55 = "Let me think about it" (requires consideration)
- Keep it impulse-purchase level

*Quality Requirements*:
- Must be OUTSTANDING
- Must over-deliver on expectations
- Must leave them thinking "How is this only £20?"
- Must showcase Bo's expertise undeniably

*Topics (Examples)*:
- Authentic Vietnamese pho: secrets of the broth
- Bánh mì mastery: perfecting the baguette
- Vietnamese coffee culture and business
- Spring rolls: traditional techniques
- F&B food cost control fundamentals

=== The Progression Path

After the trial workshop, attendees receive:

*Soft Offer for 1-on-1 Consultation*:
- 45-minute private session with Bo
- Discuss their specific F&B goals and challenges
- Assessment of fit for deeper engagement
- No pressure - genuine consultation
- If there's alignment → invitation to Playground

*Why This Works*:
- They've already experienced Bo's teaching
- They've invested £20 (skin in the game)
- They're qualified and interested
- The 1-on-1 is consultative, not pushy
- Natural progression feels earned, not sold

#pagebreak()

== Tier 2: PLAYGROUND - £20 Per Workshop

=== The Freedom Model

Instead of: "Buy my 4-week package for £200" \
We offer: "Choose any workshop you want, £20 each"

*Key Principles*:
- Each workshop is standalone
- Different topics every week
- Customers choose what interests them
- No commitment required
- Natural accumulation over time

=== How It Works

*Weekly Schedule Example*:

*Week 1: AI for Restaurants* \
Guest expert teaches practical AI applications for F&B businesses. \
Price: £20 | Duration: 90 minutes | Platform: Online

*Week 2: Cocktails & Beverages* \
Bo teaches Vietnamese coffee and creative drink menus. \
Price: £20 | Duration: 90 minutes | Platform: Hybrid

*Week 3: Food Safety Level 2* \
Certified instructor covers food hygiene essentials. \
Price: £20 | Duration: 90 minutes | Platform: Online

*Week 4: Marketing for F&B* \
Social media and local marketing strategies. \
Price: £20 | Duration: 90 minutes | Platform: Online

*Week 5: Menu Engineering* \
Designing profitable menus with psychology. \
Price: £20 | Duration: 90 minutes | Platform: Online

=== Customer Choice Scenarios

*Scenario A - The Selective Learner*: \
Mai only attends "AI for Restaurants" (£20 total) \
She got exactly what she needed.

*Scenario B - The Regular Student*: \
John attends 3 workshops over 2 months (£60 total) \
He chose topics relevant to his coffee shop.

*Scenario C - The Committed Entrepreneur*: \
Sarah attends 10 workshops over 3 months (£200 total) \
She's essentially bought the "full package" but felt in control the whole time.

=== Why Playground Beats Packages

*Traditional Package Problems*:
- "I'm not sure I need all 4 sessions"
- "What if I can't make Week 3?"
- "This is too much commitment"
- "I feel pressured to buy"

*Playground Advantages*:
- "I'll just try the AI one"
- "Oh, next week's topic looks good too"
- "I can skip any week I want"
- "I'm in control of my learning"

=== The Mathematics

*Same Revenue, Better Experience*:
- Old model: £200 package × 5 students = £1,000
- New model: £20/workshop × 50 attendances = £1,000

*But the new model offers*:
- Lower barrier to entry
- Less resistance
- More flexibility
- Better word-of-mouth
- Higher perceived value
- Stronger customer relationships

